  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improving the strategic use of information communication technology (ICT) for monitoring projects</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This capacity-strengthening project, part of the Central America Livelihoods programme, aims to implement an innovative monitoring system - Virtual System for Farm Monitoring (VSFM) &#x2013; for 10 partners in the region. The virtual platform will use different tools and methods to set up a monitoring system that will be highly visual, and will provide reports to track project progress at three levels &#x2013; farmers, partners and donors. 

The VSFM will be new in the region, so CAFOD&#x2019;s partner SIMAS will need to work closely with the targeted partners on development and implementation. CAFOD has prioritised two Nicaraguan partners with whom to pilot it, before rollout to the remainder. The project will involve detailed design and implementation activities, followed by a series of workshops to scale up to the remaining partners, tailor the system to their needs, and assess the monitoring results.</narrative>
  </description>
